<font color="#FF0000">POSTWAR GENERATION</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 19 13:21:29 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I am 24 and a member of the post war generation being born ob 8 DEC 73.  I have studied the war extensively through readings on the internet,  books,  and talking to vets.  I am an Eagle Scout and although my Dad did not serve (due to medical reasons) I have had an interest in the war.  This interest was sparked a lot in part to my friends dads who served.  We would go on campouts and the dads would sit around and talk a lot about Vietnam and I would listen eagerly.  You hear a lot about vets not talking but these guys seem to be helped by talking amongst themselves.  They can tell stories so in detail that I feel as though I have been to Vietnam.  I respect and appreciate the job our guys did when they went to Vietnam.  They were asked and they went.  This is the toughest and hardest thing these guys probably ever done in their lives.  Everyone should respect our vets and learn from them the real story of vietnam.  Only they can tell us what really happened because they were there not the politicians!  Heres a salute to the Vietnam Veterans, our country's finest men!  
<p><code>-- lbell@hubcap.clemson.edu  (K. Bell) </code><p>


